hpnsaSCDrvNumOfDrives.name: hpnsaSCDrvNumOfDrives
hpnsaSCDrvNumOfDrives.description: This specifies the number of logical drives or volumes in this system.

hpnsaSCDrvTable.name: hpnsaSCDrvTable
hpnsaSCDrvTable.description: A table of storage capacity logical drive information entries.

hpnsaSCDrvIndex.name: hpnsaSCDrvIndex
hpnsaSCDrvIndex.description: A unique index for the logical drive.

hpnsaSCDrvName.name: hpnsaSCDrvName
hpnsaSCDrvName.description: A string indicating the name of the logical drive

hpnsaSCDrvTrapsEnabled.name: hpnsaSCDrvTrapsEnabled
hpnsaSCDrvTrapsEnabled.description: This parameter specifies whether storage capacity traps are generated (enabled 1) or not (disabled 0).

hpnsaSCDrvTrapsPollTime.name: hpnsaSCDrvTrapsPollTime
hpnsaSCDrvTrapsPollTime.description: This specifies the time in minutes in which a logical drive is polled to check if thresholds have been exceeded.

hpnsaSCDrvHistSampleTime.name: hpnsaSCDrvHistSampleTime
hpnsaSCDrvHistSampleTime.description: This specifies the time in minutes in which a logical drive is sampled to maintain historical data.

hpnsaSCDrvLoThreshold.name: hpnsaSCDrvLoThreshold
hpnsaSCDrvLoThreshold.description: This specifies the lower threshold (a percentage of the total capacity of the logical drive) which has to be exceeded to trigger off an informational trap

hpnsaSCDrvWarnThreshold.name: hpnsaSCDrvWarnThreshold
hpnsaSCDrvWarnThreshold.description: This specifies the threshold (a percentage of the total capacity of the logical drive) which has to be exceeded to trigger off a warning trap

hpnsaSCDrvCritThreshold.name: hpnsaSCDrvCritThreshold
hpnsaSCDrvCritThreshold.description: This specifies the threshold (a percentage of the total capacity of the logical drive) which has to be exceeded to trigger off a critical trap

hpnsaSCDrvTotalNumDirEntries.name: hpnsaSCDrvTotalNumDirEntries
hpnsaSCDrvTotalNumDirEntries.description: Total number of directory entries per logical drive. Only applicable to netware

hpnsaSCDrvTotalNumDirEntriesUsed.name: hpnsaSCDrvTotalNumDirEntriesUsed
hpnsaSCDrvTotalNumDirEntriesUsed.description: Number of directory entries used per logical drive. Only applicable to netware

hpnsaSCDrvCurrentTotal.name: hpnsaSCDrvCurrentTotal
hpnsaSCDrvCurrentTotal.description: The current total capacity of the logical drive in KB

hpnsaSCDrvCurrentAvailable.name: hpnsaSCDrvCurrentAvailable
hpnsaSCDrvCurrentAvailable.description: The current capacity available on the logical drive in KB

hpnsaSCDrvNumOfSamples.name: hpnsaSCDrvNumOfSamples
hpnsaSCDrvNumOfSamples.description: Total number historical samples for the logical drive.

hpnsaSCDrvClearHist.name: hpnsaSCDrvClearHist
hpnsaSCDrvClearHist.description: Setting this variable to the decimal value 1234 will trigger the agent to immediately delete the samples for the logical drive. Getting the value will always return a 0.

hpnsaSCHistEntry.description: Storage Capacity logical drive historical information.

hpnsaSCHistDriveIndex.description: A unique index for the logical drive.

hpnsaSCHistSample.name: hpnsaSCHistSample
hpnsaSCHistSample.description: A block of data containing one historical drive sample. The structure of the bytes are: octets contents range __________________________________________ Local date and time on which sample was taken. 1 years since 1900 0..255 2 month 1..12 3 day 1..31 4 hour 0..23 5 minute 0..59 6 second 0..59 7-10 Total capacity in Kbytes. The 32-bit integer format is: Octet 7 (LSB) Octet 10 (MSB) 11-14 Available space in Kbytes. The 32-bit integer format is: Octet 11 (LSB) Octet 14 (MSB)
